{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781683255,"nonce":"rftcUXNVIFajOJ99CWghh1miUic=","title":"MySQL backend lags PostgreSQL feature surface","message":"Backend coverage is uneven. squealy-postgresql is the most complete (query.rs ~2.4k LOC, sql.rs ~1.4k, plus canonical.rs ~1.2k). squealy-mysql is materially smaller (query.rs ~0.5k, sql.rs ~1.1k) and likely lags on features the pg backend has (e.g. partial indexes are pg-only and MySQL rejects them per README).\n\nAudit squealy-mysql against the squealy-postgresql feature surface and either close the gaps or explicitly document each MySQL limitation (as partial indexes already are). Where behavior legitimately differs, it should be expressed through the Backend trait rather than leaking pg-isms into core.","files":null}]}